translated: Holmquist, Carl Gunnar, savings bank director, Falkenberg, born on June 3, 1888 in Gothenburg to August H. and Emilia Sofia (née Andersdotter Krans). Married for 15 years to Ester Möller. Children: Bertil, born in 1916, air force reserve lieutenant and law graduate, Tor, born in 1918, cavalry reserve lieutenant and Master of Arts, Marianne, born in 1923, married to Master of Arts H.T. Mlsison from Lund, and Gerd, born in 1926, private secretary. Completed his high school studies and graduated from Gothenburg's School of Business in 1906. Worked as a clerk at A-B Gothenburg Bank in Falkenberg from 1907 to 1914, was an accountant and deputy CEO at Falkenberg's savings bank from 1915 and CEO since 1921. Member of the board of Swedish Savings Banks Association, chairman of the board of Halland's first savings bank from 1942 to 1944, vice chairman of Västkusten's savings bank association, treasurer of Halland's air defense association, member of the city council from 1927 to 1942, vice chairman in 1929, long-standing member of the finance committee and numerous other appointments. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa 3rd class with a ribbon, the Swedish savings banks association's medal of merit, the Swedish Aeronautical Federation's gold medal.
